      <title>Rest in Peace Ertoocs</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=OT&amp;message.id=164853#M164853</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;One of the oldest guilds still in existence on Karana (now The Rathe) is House al-Nasir. I founded the guild a few days after EQ launch, and it's been in existence since then. Ertoocs, who played a Druid in EQ, left to play EQ2 where he founded and ran the House al-Nasir.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;The player behind Ertoocs tragically died on November 29th. A dedicated member of the Druids Grove for EQ2, a tireless friend and companion to many players in both EQ and EQ2, his passing is truly a loss to those who knew him, gamed with him, and loved him as a friend.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Safe journey my friend, your absence will forever be felt.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;EM&gt;Bradley Michael Witschner, 36, Kansas City, MO, passed away November 29, 2006 at home. A visitation will be 3-5PM Sunday December 3, 2006 at McGilley Antioch Chapel, with a prayer service at 5PM. Burial in Resurrection North Cemetery, Monday at 12 Noon. Bradley was born September 25, 1970. He served in the United States Air Force for 11 years active duty and 6 years active reserves. He was employed by Time Warner Cable for the past 6 years. His passion was bowling and computers. Bradley is survived by his wife Jamie, and 2 daughters, Michelle and Jessica all of the home; parents Gerald and Patricia Witschner, Kansas City, MO. Bradley was a loving husband, father, and son and will be greatly missed by his family and friends.&lt;/EM&gt; &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Hassan al-Nasir&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
